##When cancer patients hit the "pause button" by the epidemic

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to clear the fog, to seek the truth, to watch the Times.

Anxiety was a common emotion during the outbreak

"anxiety" is the emotion that haunts Linlin (not his real name) throughout the Spring Festival.

Linlin's mother, a lung cancer patient, had just taken her for a checkup in December before the outbreak, and the doctor said, "It's under control. I'd like to keep taking my medication. ". Not surprisingly, the mother was able to continue her cancer-bearing life as steadily as she had been for the past five years with lung cancer targeted drugs.

But the sudden outbreak of the disease has disrupted that plan. On Feb. 4, the mother's lung cancer targeted drug lasted only three days, but as new cases of pneumonia were identified and more hospitals were requisitioned, resources were skewed in favor of patients with the disease, "going out to the hospital to buy medicine" becomes extremely difficult. Linlin was worried that if she didn't take her medication, her mother would have another relapse.

For Cancer Patients, anxiety is a common emotion during an outbreak. On the one hand, they face a high risk of infection. On the other hand, road closures and the suspension of routine medical services have exposed them to the risk of medical shortages and deterioration of their condition, to meet the medical needs of cancer patients has become an urgent and practical problem.

And as for their care, there are people already on the move.

With over 1,000 people each

During the outbreak, Song became even busier. In his words, he used to take a break from work when he came home, but now he picks up his phone when he gets home and replies to his patients'messages.

Song Qibin is director of the cancer center of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University and President of the Hubei Society of Clinical Oncology. Wuhan as the focus of the new pneumonia epidemic area, January 23 announced the closure of the city, many hospitals also followed the outpatient service, which for cancer patients, is even worse.

On January 28, the medical treatment team of the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters issued a notice, demanding better medical care for special patients during the outbreak, specifically mentioned to meet the chronic renal failure patients, pregnant and lying-in women, surgical diseases and other groups of health care services.

But in the face of the spread of the epidemic, non-critical patients are not recommended at this time to the hospital, off-line diagnosis and treatment is no longer busy, some activities to the line.

Song Qibin said that considering that lung cancer is not only the largest type of cancer, with the largest number of patients, but also the susceptible population of the new pneumonia, once the infection is easy to develop severe. So he teamed up with nearly 150 experts on the Integrated Lung Cancer Center, or ILCC platform, of the Hubei Society of Clinical Oncology, to launch an online diagnosis and treatment model for Lung Cancer patients.

"They really needed help, but we couldn't get to the patients, so we tried a lot, " Song said.

According to the different demands of different patients, the team experts give corresponding medical advice. For some patients who have been identified but have not been admitted in time, missing the optimal window for treatment will become more dangerous; for those who have been treated and need regular follow-up, need to be based on the specific condition of the proposed moderate delay or timely drug renewal.

He also organized a group of experts from the Hubei Society of Clinical Oncology to write a medical expert advice on the home lifestyle of cancer patients during the epidemic, giving detailed medical advice on eating, tonifying and exercising. At the same time, "tumor immunotherapy" , "tumor anti-vascular treatment" and "breast cancer diagnosis and treatment" and so on, with a view to the epidemic of cancer patients with professional guidance.

Like Li Chun, also a doctor at the first aid center of a top three hospital in Wuhan, who was diagnosed with new pneumonia while working on the front line of the epidemic and chose to be quarantined at home so as not to take up scarce bed space, and during the isolation of patients with fever continue to provide online consultation. He said, "To ensure the quality of our care, the hospital limited us to seeing a maximum of 50 people a day, and as soon as I went online I adjusted to 200. But I didn't realize it was above the legal limit. The next day, I adjusted it to 300... and now I'll have as many patients as I can get. Turn on your phone, and there's a constant stream of requests, and the phone just won't keep up."

Out of the sense of responsibility of doctors, they hope to help more patients through online consultation platform. "We have more than 1,000 people interacting with each online event, " Song said, adding that through the online outpatient service, patients and doctors can have detailed exchanges, although not face-to-face, "But it's something we can do. "

500,000 public service announcements

In addition to government departments and medical institutions, many enterprises are actively participating in the treatment of cancer patients, helping more and more doctors to join the online free clinic, and using professional knowledge to help patients solve the diagnosis and treatment problems.

Mi Jian founder Liu Wengui with such a beginner's mind. As one of the earliest online communities for cancer patients, especially for lung cancer patients, Mijian is a platform for the mutual exchange and management of cancer and serious patients, and for out-hospital rehabilitation, sharing of rehabilitation experience.

After the outbreak, Liu Wengui found that patient activity on the platform doubled, discussions focused on "what's the situation with the doctor? " "What should I do now that I don't have any medicine? " "Will the postponement of the review have any impact? " ... Because of the city blockade, traffic control, resource constraints and other reasons, many patients and their families are worried about the situation they will face after the medicine is taken or the treatment is delayed.

Based on this situation, Mijian has carried out a series of targeted activities. For patients with different needs, the open information inquiry tool of tumor-related outpatient service is opened, so that patients can know the information of the nearby hospital in time With all over the country cancer drug retail pharmacy map index tools and local long prescription policy inquiries, guide patients to buy drugs convenient.

One of the most important is, by the Shanghai Jiaotong University Chest Hospital, Professor Lu Shun, director of the national expert-led Free Free Clinic activities. The event is jointly organized by the Lung Cancer Youth Committee of the Chinese Anti-cancer Association, the Lung Cancer Professional Committee of the Chinese Anti-cancer Association, the Primary Health Care, and the Lung Cancer Professional Committee of the Oncology Society of the Chinese Medical Association, find Health, Zero Krypton, astrazeneca joint support for lung cancer patients to carry out real concerns of the online public service live and online free free clinic.

"Due to the inconvenience of travel and the fact that many hospitals have reduced the number of out-patient consultations, lung cancer patients are confused about the delay of their illness and self-protection under the epidemic situation. To this end, we have joined more than 100 cancer experts from all over the country to make free one-to-one free free free free free free free free consultations in their spare time, so that patients can have the opportunity to communicate with experts from all over the country on the Internet to guide patients to receive standardized treatment, " Lu said in the first live broadcast.

Professor Lu Shun in the "lung where Strength Disease Q & a" to do online public service live broadcast

Li Xu (not his real name) , a 55-year-old lung cancer patient living in Zhoushan, Zhejiang Province, is one of the beneficiaries.

Li Xu diagnosed multiple lung cancer at the end of 2018, has been treated in Shanghai Chest Hospital, currently too many nodules have been unable to surgery, continue to take the original research targeted drug Iressa treatment. Because from the diagnosis to follow-up treatment has been carried out in Shanghai, but now affected by the epidemic, Shanghai to be quarantined for 14 days to see a doctor, there will be delays.

Through the health experts online free clinic channels, Li Xu wish to achieve medical treatment, and through the online pharmacy distribution service, do not leave the house to get the drugs, but also to avoid the risk of cross-infection in the process of travel to Shanghai and the hospital.

Liu said 48 live broadcasts on cancer have been held on the platform and have been viewed more than 500,000 times.

Racing with cancer patients, racing with life

Recently, there has been good news in the fight against the epidemic. In many parts of the country, new cases have been "zeroed out. " Zhang Boli, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said in an interview with the media that Wuhan is also expected to have new cases "zeroed out" by the end of March.

With the improvement of the epidemic situation, the squeezing of medical resources will be eased, and the normal medical order for cancer patients will be gradually restored. On February 17, the Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission released a list of medical institutions in the province that receive patients with non-new-crown pneumonia, calling on all localities to do a good job in providing medical care to patients with non-new-crown pneumonia during the epidemic.

A list of some medical institutions in Hubei Province receiving non-new-crown pneumonia patients (from the website of Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission)

Song Qibin's Wuhan University People's Hospital, which is a designated treatment hospital for severe cases of new coronavirus pneumonia, also announced on its website on March 10 that the Shouyiyuan district (old hospital district) of the hospital will be gradually and orderly restored to a general outpatient clinic.

But help for cancer patients continues. Song Qibin said nearly 30 free clinic activities have been prepared on the ILCC platform of the Integrated Lung Cancer Diagnosis and Treatment Center of the Hubei Society of Clinical Oncology, "every day. ".

And Zhejiang, which is more than 700 kilometers away from Hubei, is also organizing the public welfare activity of "lung cancer experts online video patient education and interactive question-and-answer" by relying on the project of the Integrated Lung Cancer Diagnosis and Treatment Center (ILCC) of the Zhejiang Anti-cancer Association, and organizing the authoritative lung cancer experts of the province, through the form of video network face-to-face questions and answers, for Lung Cancer Patients Answer Questions, trouble-shooting.

"The public welfare live broadcast and the Free Clinic Platform will arrange three to four sessions a week, and the online diagnosis and treatment will continue to be popular, and will not fall down rapidly with the recovery of the outpatient service. " Liu believes that in the future, online diagnosis and treatment will become a medical supplement for offline medical care.

Under the epidemic, no one can stay out of the way, this is a group war "epidemic. ". From front-line medical and nursing staff supporting the epidemic areas, to people from all walks of life who donate money and materials, from busy to "broken legs" delivery boys, to individuals fighting the epidemic at home, and the doctors, businesses, and people who became incredibly busy during the epidemic for the UNCROWNED, are all working toward the same goal, all contributing, all being heroes.

The epidemic will eventually pass, and when we look back to the beginning of 2020, we will always remember it as warm and moving.

"Due to the inconvenience of travel and the fact that many hospitals have reduced the number of out-patient consultations, lung cancer patients are confused about the delay of their illness and self-protection under the epidemic situation. To this end, we have joined more than 100 cancer experts from all over the country to make free one-to-one free free free free free free free free consultations in their spare time, so that patients can have the opportunity to communicate with experts from all over the country on the Internet to guide patients to receive standardized treatment, " Lu said in the first live broadcast.

Li Xu (not his real name) , a 55-year-old lung cancer patient living in Zhoushan, Zhejiang Province, is one of the beneficiaries.

Li Xu diagnosed multiple lung cancer at the end of 2018, has been treated in Shanghai Chest Hospital, currently too many nodules have been unable to surgery, continue to take the original research targeted drug Iressa treatment. Because from the diagnosis to follow-up treatment has been carried out in Shanghai, but now affected by the epidemic, Shanghai to be quarantined for 14 days to see a doctor, there will be delays.

Through the health experts online free clinic channels, Li Xu wish to achieve medical treatment, and through the online pharmacy distribution service, do not leave the house to get the drugs, but also to avoid the risk of cross-infection in the process of travel to Shanghai and the hospital.

Liu said 48 live broadcasts on cancer have been held on the platform and have been viewed more than 500,000 times.

Racing with cancer patients, racing with life

Recently, there has been good news in the fight against the epidemic. In many parts of the country, new cases have been "zeroed out. " Zhang Boli, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said in an interview with the media that Wuhan is also expected to have new cases "zeroed out" by the end of March.

With the improvement of the epidemic situation, the squeezing of medical resources will be eased, and the normal medical order for cancer patients will be gradually restored. On February 17, the Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission released a list of medical institutions in the province that receive patients with non-new-crown pneumonia, calling on all localities to do a good job in providing medical care to patients with non-new-crown pneumonia during the epidemic.

Racing with cancer patients, racing with life

Recently, there has been good news in the fight against the epidemic. In many parts of the country, new cases have been "zeroed out. " Zhang Boli, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said in an interview with the media that Wuhan is also expected to have new cases "zeroed out" by the end of March.

With the improvement of the epidemic situation, the squeezing of medical resources will be eased, and the normal medical order for cancer patients will be gradually restored. On February 17, the Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission released a list of medical institutions in the province that receive patients with non-new-crown pneumonia, calling on all localities to do a good job in providing medical care to patients with non-new-crown pneumonia during the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A list of some medical institutions in Hubei Province receiving non-new-crown pneumonia patients (from the website of Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission)

Song Qibin's Wuhan University People's Hospital, which is a designated treatment hospital for severe cases of new coronavirus pneumonia, also announced on its website on March 10 that the Shouyiyuan district (old hospital district) of the hospital will be gradually and orderly restored to a general outpatient clinic.

But help for cancer patients continues. Song Qibin said nearly 30 free clinic activities have been prepared on the ILCC platform of the Integrated Lung Cancer Diagnosis and Treatment Center of the Hubei Society of Clinical Oncology, "every day. ".

And Zhejiang, which is more than 700 kilometers away from Hubei, is also organizing the public welfare activity of "lung cancer experts online video patient education and interactive question-and-answer" by relying on the project of the Integrated Lung Cancer Diagnosis and Treatment Center (ILCC) of the Zhejiang Anti-cancer Association, and organizing the authoritative lung cancer experts of the province, through the form of video network face-to-face questions and answers, for Lung Cancer Patients Answer Questions, trouble-shooting.

"The public welfare live broadcast and the Free Clinic Platform will arrange three to four sessions a week, and the online diagnosis and treatment will continue to be popular, and will not fall down rapidly with the recovery of the outpatient service. " Liu believes that in the future, online diagnosis and treatment will become a medical supplement for offline medical care.

Under the epidemic, no one can stay out of the way, this is a group war "epidemic. ". From front-line medical and nursing staff supporting the epidemic areas, to people from all walks of life who donate money and materials, from busy to "broken legs" delivery boys, to individuals fighting the epidemic at home, and the doctors, businesses, and people who became incredibly busy during the epidemic for the UNCROWNED, are all working toward the same goal, all contributing, all being heroes.

The epidemic will eventually pass, and when we look back to the beginning of 2020, we will always remember it as warm and moving.
